dev.marksman.kraftwerk.constraints

Class CharRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.marksman.kraftwerk.constraints.CharRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Constraint<java.lang.Character>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Character>

    public final class CharRange
extends java.lang.Object
implements Constraint<java.lang.Character>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Character>
    A range of chars. Like all ranges, it is immutable and its span always includes a minimum of one value.

    Construct using one of the static methods (inclusive(char, char), exclusive(char, char)),

    or by using from(char): 

     CharRange.from('a').to('z')      // 'a'..'z' inclusive
 CharRange.from('a').until('z')   // 'a'..'z' exclusive
